Looking at your code, you‚Äôre probably getting a file not found type exception.

  1. Uncomment your autonomousInit() method in Main.
  2. Your autonomousInit() method is calling method getAutonomousCommand() in ReportContainer. Inside that method, you are attempting to load an auto named ‚ÄúNew Auto‚Äù. No auto path named that exists in your deploy/pathplanner/autos directory. Change ‚ÄúNew Auto‚Äù to ‚ÄúTests‚Äù because you do have an auto path named that.
  3. In SwerveSubsystem, you added line 63. That line is doing basically doing the same thing as what happens inside the setupPathPlanner method which is called immediately after your added line. You can probably delete what you added to SwerveSubsystem.

Your AutoChooser still won‚Äôt be working after these changes, but the code crashing might stop.

Latest github download shows you are on WPILIb 2025.1.1 - as of yesterday this is now 2 releases behind.
Start by updating that, PathPlanner and any out-of-date Vendor libraries.
Looks like you might not be using Simulation since the SmartDashboard Field2d doesn‚Äôt support the Reefscape Field image. If not, learn to use it,
Also in RobotContainer use autoChooser.getSelected();
as the getAutonomousCommand return. Then you will only get the ones PathPlanner has filtered by your ‚ÄúTest‚Äù conditions.
When I do that, simulation runs the Test Rotation auto.
